(Ford GoBike System Data)¶

by (Youssef Hussein Ahmed)¶

Dataset Overview¶

This data set includes information about individual rides made in a bike-sharing system covering the greater San Francisco Bay area.

2- Distribution of "start_time" and "end_time"¶

  • These variables has unfamiliar dtype (datetime64)..
  • I treated them as ordinal variables with intervals of hours or days.
  • By seprating each variable into 2 additional cols for ex: start_time can be seprated into:
    • start_time encoded into categorical variable with dayparts as categories.
    • day encoded into categorical variable with (Weekday, Weekend) as categories.

# add approximate cols of lat_vars values to form 4 unique values and do same to long_vars
step = 0.2
to_bin = lambda x: np.floor(x / step) * step

for var in ['start_station_latitude', 'end_station_latitude']:
    feat_df[var+'_region'] = feat_df[var].map(to_bin)
    
for var in ['start_station_longitude', 'end_station_longitude']:
    feat_df[var+'_region'] = feat_df[var].map(to_bin)

In [24]:
# convert numeric values to string
def to_region(x, long= False):
    '''This function group each unique numeric
        value of latitude or longitude to its appropriate
        lat or long region'''
    if long:
        if x== -122.: return 'long_region3'
        elif x== -122.4: return 'long_region2'
        else: return 'long_region1'
    else:
        if x==37.2: return 'lat_region1'
        elif x==37.6: return 'lat_region2'
        else: return 'lat_region3'

for var in ['start_station_latitude_region', 'end_station_latitude_region']:
    feat_df[var] = feat_df[var].apply(to_region)
    
for var in ['start_station_longitude_region', 'end_station_longitude_region']:
    feat_df[var] = feat_df[var].apply(to_region, long= True)

# convert lat_long_vars to ordinal types
lat_regions = ['lat_region1', 'lat_region2', 'lat_region3']
long_regions = ['long_region1', 'long_region2', 'long_region3']

lat_regions_type = pd.api.types.CategoricalDtype(ordered= True, categories= lat_regions)
long_regions_type = pd.api.types.CategoricalDtype(ordered= True, categories= long_regions)

for var in ['start_station_latitude_region', 'end_station_latitude_region']:
    feat_df[var] = feat_df[var].astype(lat_regions_type)
    
for var in ['start_station_longitude_region', 'end_station_longitude_region']:
    feat_df[var] = feat_df[var].astype(long_regions_type)
